<p>I'm using PHPUnit and I have to check a <code>json_decode</code> result. I have an object containing an integer attribute as you can see in the debugger view :</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/e0Pqv.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/e0Pqv.png" alt="Debugger view of my object"></a></p>  <p>When I do this : </p>  <pre><code>$this-&gt;assertObjectHasAttribute('1507',$object); </code></pre>  <p>I get an error :</p>  <pre><code>PHPUnit_Framework_Assert::assertObjectHasAttribute() must be a valid attribute name </code></pre>  <p>My <code>$object</code> is an instance of <code>stdClass</code></p>